This is saying that room doesn&#39;t know which method to use to get the **flagTest** value. It has the choice between **getFlagTest** and **isFlagtest**.

If you want both methods to be available then you can use the **`@Ignore`** annotation to tell room to ignore one (it shouldn&#39;t matter which).

e.g. 

    @Entity
    public class MyEntity {
    
        @PrimaryKey(autoGenerate = true)
        private long id;
    
        boolean flagTest;
    
    
        public long getId() {
            return id;
        }
    
        public void setId(long dummyid) {
            this.id = dummyid;
        }
    
        @Ignore
        public boolean getFlagTest() {
            return flagTest;
        }
    
        public boolean isFlagTest() {
            return flagTest;
        }
    }

- typically `is????` is used for **boolean**&#39;d as the value can only be either true or false, hence the **getFlagTest** method has had the annotation supplied.

